headline: Why Serve Robotics (SERV) Is Down 12.6 Percent After Issuing Bold Expansion and Revenue Guidance
summary: Serve Robotics announced third-quarter 2025 results alongside new guidance, highlighting rapid expansion of its robot fleet, major partnerships with DoorDash and Uber, and an anticipated tenfold revenue increase in 2026. The company’s shift into what management calls a “scale with precision” phase emphasizes a sharpened focus on growth while boosting per-robot productivity and entering new metro markets such as Chicago. We’ll examine how Serve Robotics’ ambitious plans to deploy 2,000 robots...
